nt\ntwist-angles in graphene/hBN superlattices, which converge to the same value\nafter thermal annealing. This observation confirms the self-locking mechanism\nof graphene/hBN superlattices also in the presence of strain gradients. Our\nexperiments may have profound implications in the development of future\nelectronic devices based on heterostructures and provide a new mechanism to\ninduce complex strain patterns in 2D materials.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Oct 2018 10:52:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 18 Oct 2018 15:34:32 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 4 Dec 2018 10:20:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-18"}
