of the HR diagram. We find that both the primary and the\nsecondary components deviate from the evolutionary tracks corresponding to\ntheir masses in the sense that the stars appear in the diagram at lower masses\nthan their true masses.\n  Conclusions. We further evaluate the proposition that active giants have\nmasses that are found to be generally higher by traditional methods than are\nindicated by stellar evolution tracks in the HR diagram. A possible reason for\nthis discrepancy could be a strong magnetic field, since we see greater\ndifferences in more active stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Oct 2018 11:42:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-19"}
